Content:
San Michael Walsh born 3 July 1802 in Ogden, Halifax, West Yorkshire, England. He was well known locally as a poet, writer and artist in the rural Pennines often his work was inspired by the local country life. Furthermore, according to several diary entries - he was a good friend of the Bront family. He died in 1872. His work can still be found today at the Dean Clough Gallery in Halifax. His most famous article was a watercolor work of the Causeway Foot, Ogden moor. It is believed to have been painted around 1854 and is entitled "The Moorlands of Halifax".
